cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper focuses on planning problems in robotics, specifically in continuous state-action spaces. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a machine learning approach, using a Generative Adversarial Network (GAN), to guide the search of a state-space planner. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a GAN to learn an action-sampling distribution that can generalize across different instances of a planning problem. 
4. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - Although not the main focus, the paper mentions using visual input in one of the evaluated robot planning problems. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper addresses the issue of efficiently planning in high-dimensional continuous state-action spaces for long horizons, which is relevant to the field of systems and control.
